The article is a statement made by the President of the United States on the Month of the Military Child. The President expresses gratitude towards the men and women in uniform who serve the nation and acknowledges the sacrifice their families make as well. He specifically mentions the strength and courage displayed by military children who often have to move frequently and may not see their loved ones for long periods of time. The President calls on all Americans to keep military children in their thoughts and prayers and to offer support to them and their families.